  "texts": [
    "Sagmeister et al. [83] reported the optimization of a two-step telescoped synthesis of the active pharmaceutical ingredient edaravone (52, Table 2, entry 10).",
    "In this study, a self-optimizing flow reactor was used to run the optimization of seven continuous variables, including three variables for the first step and four variables for the second step.",
    "The optimization had the objective of maximizing the yield of the imine intermediate 51 obtained after the first reaction, the STY of 52, and minimizing the overall used equivalents of the reagents.",
    "After 85 iterations, a maximum yield of 95% for the synthesis of 51 and a maximum STY of 5.42 kg/h for the synthesis of edaravone (52) were achieved.",
    "Setting the objective to reducing the quantity of reagents led to the discovery of unexpected reaction conditions where a substoichiometric amount of triethylamine was sufficient to promote the second reaction step, decreasing the waste produced during synthesis."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Sagmeister et al. [83] reported the optimization of a two-step telescoped synthesis of the active pharmaceutical ingredient edaravone (52, Table 2, entry 10)."
  ]
}